    caseStudy: 'Case Study: Houston Community Hospital Network (6 locations, 180 providers, 5,400 patient visits/week). Challenge: 22-minute average intake creating 35-minute appointment delays. 14% data error rate causing $4,500/month rework + downstream issues. Insurance verification failures (9%) requiring rework on 486 visits/month. Multilingual population (48% non-English) causing interpretation delays and accuracy concerns. Intervention: Dr. Capital VA intake management (10 FTE, 50 hours/week across 6 locations). Results: Intake time reduced 22 min → 14 min (8-minute schedule buffer created). Data accuracy improved 86% → 98%. Insurance verification failure dropped 9% → 1.2%. Multilingual intake improved: dedicated Spanish-bilingual VAs + professional interpretation system reduced language barriers. Patient satisfaction (intake experience) improved 6.8 → 8.4/10. Schedule efficiency: 280 additional billable visits/month = $56,000/month = $672,000/year. Billing rework reduced 14% → 2%, saving $4,000/month. Year 1 financial impact: $672,000 schedule efficiency + $48,000 rework reduction + staff time reallocation. Cost: $36,000. ROI: 1,889%.',
    toolsEhr: 'Houston facilities use Epic (most common), Cerner, athenahealth, and Medidata. VAs interact with intake modules that feed directly to EHR. Insurance verification integrates with MultiPlan, UnitedHealth Claims Connect, and Aetna eServices. Texas Medicaid verification routes through TMHP. Patient data management platforms like Salesforce Health Cloud integrate with EHRs for pre-visit data collection.',
    faq: [
      { question: 'How do VAs verify insurance for Texas Medicaid CHIP beneficiaries?', answer: 'VAs access TMHP (Texas Medicaid & Healthcare Partnership) portal directly, confirm member ID status, verify active coverage, confirm PCP assignment when relevant, and identify any coverage gaps. For mixed coverage (Medicare + Medicaid), we verify both systems to understand coordination of benefits.' },
      { question: 'What happens when a patient has complex prior medical history across Texas Medical Center?', answer: 'VAs conduct thorough medication reconciliation using prior records available in shared systems, contact previous providers for missing information, and ensure allergies and reactions are clearly documented. We prevent duplicate testing and ensure continuity of care.' },
      { question: 'How are financial barriers addressed during intake for uninsured patients?', answer: 'VAs discuss hospital financial assistance programs (most Houston hospitals offer 200%+ Federal Poverty Level charity care), government programs (Medicaid pathway assessment), community health center options, and payment plan flexibility. VAs provide clear information on all options and connect patients with financial counselors.' },
      { question: 'Can VAs manage interpretation services for non-English speakers during intake?', answer: 'Yes. VAs arrange professional medical interpreters (phone or in-person) for non-English visits, ensuring interpretation quality and HIPAA compliance. We do not rely on family members for clinical interpretation due to accuracy/liability concerns. Spanish-bilingual VAs handle routine Spanish intake directly.' }
    ],
    interlinking: 'Clean intake creates clean billing—Medical Billing VAs process claims faster with accurate demographics. Patient Scheduling improves efficiency with complete prior data. Patient Follow-Up builds on accurate medication/allergy information. Referral Coordination uses clean insurance/authorization data from intake.'
